SIMPLE: favorite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Favorite
<hw>Fa"vor*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>favorit</ets> favored, F. <ets>favori</ets>, fem.
<ets>favorite</ets>, p. p. of OF. <ets>favorir</ets>, cf. It.
<ets>favorito</ets>, frm. <ets>favorita</ets>, fr. <ets>favorire</ets>
to favor. See <er>Favor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person or thing
regarded with peculiar favor; one treated with partiality; one preferred
above others; especially, one unduly loved, trusted, and enriched with
favors by a person of high rank or authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Committing to a wicked <qex>favorite</qex>⟦br⟧
All public cares.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Short curls dangling over the
temples; -- fashionable in the reign of Charles II.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Farquhar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Sporting)</fld> <def>The competitor (as a horse in
a race) that is judged most likely to win; the competitor standing
highest in the betting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Favorite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Favorite
<hw>Fa"vor*ite</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Regarded with particular
affection, esteem, or preference; <as>as, a <ex>favorite</ex> walk; a
<ex>favorite</ex> child.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧His <xex>favorite</xex>
argument.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Favoritism</ent>⟦br⟧
